Interface StringMatchIterator<MATCHRESULT>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<MATCHRESULT>

    public interface StringMatchIterator<MATCHRESULT>
extends java.util.Iterator<MATCHRESULT>
    An Iterator that provides access to the pattern matches in a string

    StringSearcher.searchString(String) produces these.

        java.lang.String matchValue()
        Get the string value of the last match

        Note that a new string is allocated by the first call to this method for each match.

        Returns:
        the source portion of the source string corresponding to the last match
        Throws:

        Get the result of the last match.

        Throws:

      • reposition

        boolean reposition(int pos)
        rewind (or jump forward) to a given position in the source string

        The next match returned will be the one (if any) that starts at a position >= pos

        IMPORTANT: If this method returns true, you must call Iterator.next() to get the result of the next match. Until then calls to the the match accessor methods will continue to return information from the previous call to Iterator.next().

        Parameters:
        pos - new position in the source string to search from
        Returns:
        true if there is a match after the given position. The same value will be returned from {Iterator.hasNext()
